      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">25.702-3</ph> Remedies.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d1686e8" class="- topic/p ">Upon the determination of a false certification under subsection <xref href="25.702-2.dita#FAR_25_702_2"
                  base="i1091211"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">25.702-2</xref>-</p>
         <ol id="d1656e22" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1678e15">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            The contracting officer may terminate the contract;</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1678e20">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-015?>suspending and debarring official<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 25.702-3 by—   a. Removing from paragraph (b) “suspending official” and “Subpart” and adding “suspending and debarring official” and “subpart” in their places, respectively; and?></ph> may suspend the contractor in accordance with the procedures in <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph ">
                     <xref href="Subpart_9.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_9_4"
                           base="i1115147"
                           outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                           class="- topic/xref ">subpart  9.4</xref>;</ph> and</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1678e28">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-015?>The suspending and debarring<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Removing from paragraph (c) “The debarring” and “Subpart” and adding “The suspending and debarring” and “subpart” in their places, respectively.?></ph> may debar the contractor for a period not to exceed 3 years in accordance with the procedures in <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph ">
                     <xref href="Subpart_9.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_9_4"
                           base="i1115147"
                           outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                           class="- topic/xref ">subpart  9.4</xref>.</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
